Turkish Equity Movers: Akfen Holding, BIM Birlesik, Goldas Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-21T08:58:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/turkish-equity-movers-akfen-holding-bim-birlesik-goldas-move.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose for a third day, adding 478.76, or 0.8 percent, to
64,318.03 at 10:25 p.m. in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.    Akfen Holding AS (AKFEN)  , a builder and energy producer,
rose after chairman Hamdi Akin said in a Bloomberg interview
that the company will grow its business in double-digits and
will bid for Istanbul’s ferry and toll bridges in auctions this
year. The shares gained 36 kurus, or 3.6 percent, to 10.28
liras.    BIM Birlesik Magazalar AS (BIMAS)  , a discount
supermarket chain, climbed 1 lira, or 2.2 percent, to 46.90
liras after being upgraded to “buy” at Deutsche Bank AG. Deutsche
set a price estimate of 60.8 liras for the share  Goldas Kuyumculuk Sanayi Ithalat & Ihracat AS (GOLDS TI), a
gold retailer and miner, gained 8 kurus, or 8.6 percent, to 1.01
liras after saying gold reserves at a field it operates in Mali
were valued at $240.5 million. The field is owned by the Belgium
Trading Company, in which Goldas has a 70 percent stake,
according to a filing with the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the
market closed on March 18.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
